Explore the Einstein Bot Block Library

Learn about Einstein bot blocks designed for specific clouds and use cases.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

Required editions:
* Add a Case Comment
  Description: Collects a case comment and adds it to an existing case.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
* Agent Transfer
  Description: Transfers a conversation to an agent or lets the user know no agents are available.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
* Check Case Status
  Description: Collects a case number and email address from the user and returns the case status.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
* Check Order Status
  Description: Collects an order number from the user and returns the order amount and status.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
* Close Case
  Description: Closes a matched case.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
* Create Case
  Description: Checks a variable for existing cases and creates a case for a new issue.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
* CSAT Survey
  Description: Collects a user's rating of their satisfaction with the conversational experience.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
* Data Collection Disclosure
  Description: Discloses that a user’s conversation with the bot can be saved.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
* Effective Account Selection
  Description: Checks if a user has an existing account and collects the account’s information. If more than one user account is found, returns a list of accounts and collects the selected account’s information.
  Supported bot types: Enhanced
* Feedback Collection
  Description: Collects a user's feedback of their satisfaction with the conversational experience and tracks the feedback using Goals. If a user has an unsatisfactory experience, collects details about the experience from the user.
  Supported bot types: Enhanced
* Order List
  Description: Returns the user’s recent orders.
  Supported bot types: Enhanced
* Product Recommendations
  Description: Collects the user’s requests and returns product recommendations based on the request.
  Supported bot types: Enhanced
* Reorder
  Description: Collects the order number for a user’s past order and adds the items from that order to the user’s cart.
  Supported bot types: Enhanced
* User Authentication
  Description: Collects the user’s username and sends a verification code to the user’s email address.
  Supported bot types: Enhanced
* User Info Collection
  Description: Collects the user’s first name, last name, email address, phone number, and company name.
  Supported bot types: Standard or Enhanced
